///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @file BuildConfiguration.dox
 * @brief Build-time configuration options for MIDILAR (CMake and Arduino).
 *
 * This file documents all available CMake options and preprocessor macros
 * used to enable or disable features in the MIDILAR library.
 *
 * For Arduino and PlatformIO builds, these options are defined manually
 * in `System/UserSetup.h`.
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @addtogroup MIDILAR_BG_BuildConfiguration
 * @brief Reference for all compile-time MIDILAR configuration flags.
 *
 * These flags apply both to:
 * - CMake-based projects (`option(...)`)
 * - Arduino (`#define` macros)
 *
 * @note For Arduino users, you must manually define these in `System/UserSetup.h`.
 *
 * These options are declared in:
 * ```
 * {ArduinoRootDir}/libraries/MIDILAR/src/system/UserSetup.h
 * ```
 * The intended usage is to comment out unused Modules, by default all modules are enabled.
 *
 * `System/UserSetup.h` file using standard `#define` directives:
 *
 * @code{.cpp}
 * #define MIDILAR_DSP_CORE
 * #define MIDILAR_LUT
 * #define MIDILAR_MIDI_MESSAGE_PARSER
 * #define MIDILAR_GENERATORS_PERIODIC
 * @endcode
 *
 * This file is included when including "MIDILAR.h", it is included in "MIDILAR_BuildSettings.h",
 * with the help of preprocessor macros to detect when it is needed.
 */

///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @defgroup MIDILAR_BG_BC_DspCore DspCore
 * @ingroup MIDILAR_BG_BuildConfiguration
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

